From: VyOS LS1046A Build <build@vyos.io>
Date: Sat, 18 Apr 2026 04:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] usb: host: xhci-plat: force XHCI_AVOID_BEI on LS1046A DWC3

On the NXP LS1046A the Synopsys DesignWare USB3 controller posts Block
Event Interrupts (BEI) on bulk TRBs in a way the xHCI host state
machine mishandles when the TRB ring wraps: a genuine transfer event
that arrives after a BEI-suppressed event is misattributed to a stale
slot/endpoint and the xHCI internal command timer eventually fires,
marking the HC dead.

First version of this patch walked the parent chain and matched
`fsl,ls1046a-dwc3` via `of_device_is_compatible(tmpdev->of_node, ...)`,
but that match FAILED at runtime on the Mono Gateway: the xhci-hcd
platform child created by dwc3_host_init() has its of_node unset; only
its fwnode is populated (via pdevinfo.fwnode = dev_fwnode(dwc->dev)).
Walking tmpdev->of_node therefore never reached the DT node.

This version:
  1. Walks parents via both tmpdev->of_node AND tmpdev->fwnode.
  2. Also accepts `snps,dwc3` (the generic DWC3 compatible) so that
     we catch the dwc3 core platform device one level up even if
     the LS1046A-specific compatible is absent from that device's
     of_node (mainline DTS may only list `snps,dwc3` on the child).
  3. Emits a one-shot dev_info() so the quirks=... line in the boot
     log can be correlated with whether the match fired.

Bits added: XHCI_AVOID_BEI (0x8000) + XHCI_TRUST_TX_LENGTH (0x400).

Signed-off-by: VyOS LS1046A Build <build@vyos.io>
---
 drivers/usb/host/xhci-plat.c | 27 +++++++++++++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 27 insertions(+)

--- a/drivers/usb/host/xhci-plat.c
+++ b/drivers/usb/host/xhci-plat.c
@@ -76,8 +76,35 @@ static int xhci_priv_resume_quirk(struct usb_hcd *hcd)
 static void xhci_plat_quirks(struct device *dev, struct xhci_hcd *xhci)
 {
 	struct xhci_plat_priv *priv = xhci_to_priv(xhci);
+	struct device *tmpdev;
+	bool matched = false;
 
 	xhci->quirks |= priv->quirks;
+
+	/*
+	 * NXP LS1046A DWC3 errata: the controller posts BEI on bulk TRBs
+	 * in a way that confuses the xHCI event handler when the ring
+	 * wraps, leading to "xHCI host controller not responding, assume
+	 * dead" during USB-storage probe. Force XHCI_AVOID_BEI plus
+	 * XHCI_TRUST_TX_LENGTH on any xhci whose parent chain reaches a
+	 * DWC3 / LS1046A DWC3 DT node. dwc3_host_init() propagates fwnode
+	 * (not of_node) to the xhci platform child, so check both.
+	 */
+	for (tmpdev = dev; tmpdev; tmpdev = tmpdev->parent) {
+		if (tmpdev->of_node &&
+		    (of_device_is_compatible(tmpdev->of_node, "fsl,ls1046a-dwc3") ||
+		     of_device_is_compatible(tmpdev->of_node, "snps,dwc3"))) {
+			matched = true;
+			break;
+		}
+		if (tmpdev->fwnode &&
+		    (fwnode_device_is_compatible(tmpdev->fwnode, "fsl,ls1046a-dwc3") ||
+		     fwnode_device_is_compatible(tmpdev->fwnode, "snps,dwc3"))) {
+			matched = true;
+			break;
+		}
+	}
+	if (matched) {
+		xhci->quirks |= XHCI_AVOID_BEI | XHCI_TRUST_TX_LENGTH;
+		dev_info(dev, "LS1046A DWC3 quirks applied (AVOID_BEI | TRUST_TX_LENGTH)\n");
+	}
 }
 
 /* called during probe() after chip reset completes */